info.senderName: NWS Omaha (Eastern Nebraska and Southeastern Iowa - Omaha Valley)
info.headline: Flood Warning issued February 16 at 3:25PM CST by NWS Omaha
info.description: ...FLOOD WARNING FOR AN ICE JAM IN EFFECT UNTIL 1030 AM CST FRIDAY... * WHAT...Flooding caused by an ice jam is occurring. * WHERE...Portions of east central Nebraska and northeast Nebraska, including the following counties, in east central Nebraska, Butler. In northeast Nebraska, Colfax. * WHEN...Until 1030 AM CST Friday. * IMPACTS...Flooding of rivers, creeks, streams, and other low-lying and flood-prone locations is imminent or occurring. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS... - At 325 PM CST, emergency management reported an ice jam 2 mile east of the highway 15 bridge with minor flooding occurring on the north bank of the Platte River. - Flooding is occurring along the Platte River. - Some locations that will experience flooding include... mainly rural areas of Northeastern Butler and Southeastern Colfax Counties - http://www.weather.gov/safety/flood
info.instruction: Turn around, don`t drown when encountering flooded roads. Most flood deaths occur in vehicles.
